<dl id="n06039c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06039c">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06039c"> 39(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> W (sitting down) <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06039c"><li>FW 120.28 </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/lexe.htm#n06039c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/e/l39e.htm#n06039c">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n06039c">MS BL 47471b-47v</ms> </li><li>JJA 46:310 <a name="e41d" href="../../ff/fdra/eda.htm#e41d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/e/e41d.htm#n06039c">Draft: I.5&sect;4.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Les choses les plus insignifiantes s&apos;animent au souffle r&eacute;chauffant de la fantaisie enfantine. Les lettres deviennent presque des personnes. Un bambin d&apos;un an et huit mois s&apos;&eacute;tait pris d&apos;une telle passion pour la lettre w qu&apos;il l&apos;appelait toujours: &ldquo;<mark>Ce cher vieux w</mark>.&rdquo; Un autre bonhomme de quatre ans, &eacute;tant occup&eacute; &agrave; &eacute;crire la lettre L, laissa glisser sa plume de telle fa&ccedil;on que le trait horizontal form&acirc;t un angle L. L&apos;enfant vit aussit&ocirc;t qu&apos;il ressemblait &agrave; un &ecirc;tre humain au repos et di: &ldquo;Tiens! <mark>il s&apos;est assis</mark>.&rdquo; <font color="green">[The most insignificant things come alive with the warming breath of childlike fantasy. The letters become almost people. A toddler of one year and eight months had taken such a passion for the letter w that he still called it &ldquo;"This dear old w.&rdquo; Another four year old man, being busy writing the letter He let his pen slip in such a way that the horizontal line formed an angle L. The child saw as soon as he looked like a human being at rest and said, &ldquo;Here! he sat down.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 10</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
